  "text": "Implemented a minimal Envoy HTTP filter following established extension patterns from envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2. The pass_through_filter.h header file defines the PassThroughFilter class that inherits from Http::StreamDecoderFilter (defined in envoy/http/filter.h), implementing the core decoder methods: decodeHeaders(), decodeData(), and decodeTrailers(). All methods return Continue status to pass data through unchanged, following the filter return code conventions defined in Http::FilterHeadersStatus, Http::FilterDataStatus, and Http::FilterTrailersStatus enums. The implementation includes setDecoderFilterCallbacks() to receive callbacks and onDestroy() lifecycle method as shown in buffer_filter.h and kill_request_filter.h examples. The filter registration follows the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory pattern using the Common::FactoryBase template from source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h. The pass_through_config.h factory class inherits from Common::FactoryBase<google::protobuf::Empty> and overrides createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped() to create filter instances. The pass_through_config.cc file implements the factory and registers it using the REGISTER_FACTORY macro pattern (matching kill_request pattern) rather than LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY (buffer pattern). The implementation closely mirrors the kill_request extension in both structure and macro usage while maintaining minimal functionality appropriate for a pass-through filter."
